<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Paris Saint-Germain have signed Spanish goalkeeper Sergio Rico on a permanent four-year deal from Sevilla, the French champions have confirmed.   </p>

<p>Rico joined PSG on a season-long loan last September and played 10 games in all competitions, helping the side win the Ligue 1 title, the Coupe de France and the Coupe de la Ligue and reach the final of the Champions League. </p>

<p>The clubs have agreed on a fee of around £5.3m and Rico has signed a contract until 2024.</p>

<p>Sergio Rico has rejoined Paris Saint-Germain following a loan spell at the club last season</p>

<p>Rico made 170 appearances for Sevilla and also spent a season on-loan at Fulham in 2018-19</p>

<p>In a club statement PSG said: 'The club would like to congratulate Sergio and wish him every success as he continues his career with the Rouge-et-Bleu.'</p>

<p>Rico, who has won one cap for Spain, made 170 appearances for Sevilla in all competitions, winning two Europa League titles during his time with the Spanish club.</p>

<p>He fell down the pecking order during his time with the club, however and spent the 2018-19 season on-loan at Fulham when they were relegated from the Premiership.</p>
